[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+     9[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;143;161;179m##[38;2;192;197;206m [38;2;143;161;179mOverall Assessment[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    10[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    11[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;192;197;206mThis recipe takes the personalization scaffolding established in Recipes 4.1 through 4.3 and graduates it to the harder problem class: causal recommendation under capacity constraints with multi-month feedback loops. The teaching is genuinely strong on the things teams most often get wrong. The eight-stage pipeline (eligibility → need → engagement → uplift → ranking → allocation → orchestration → feedback) is the right shape for a wellness recommender, the persuadables/sure-things/lost-causes/sleeping-dogs framing is the correct uplift mental model, and the equity discussion (engagement-prediction bias, outcome-prediction bias, capacity allocation as rationing) is more honest than most production wellness systems achieve in their first three years.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    12[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    13[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;192;197;206mSeveral of the chapter-level production-hardening gaps the panel flagged across 4.1, 4.2, and 4.3 have been resolved in the main text rather than punted to "Why This Isn't Production-Ready":[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    14[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    15[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;191;97;106mThe recommendation log and engagement events are explicitly named as PHI ("a (member_id, program_id, score) row implicitly reveals clinical context"), with customer-managed KMS, CloudTrail data events, narrow IAM read scopes, and a defined retention period (90-180 days for individually-attributed; longer only after de-identification). That resolves 4.1 Finding 3, 4.3 Finding 1, and the chapter-wide PHI-in-personalization-records pattern.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    16[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m Engagement event integrity is enforced: [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mprocess_engagement_event[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m validates [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mevent.member_id != rec.member_id[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m and drops mismatches. That resolves 4.2 Finding 3 and 4.3 Finding's identity-boundary pattern.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    17[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m Bedrock data-retention posture is stated explicitly, with a TODO to verify per-model coverage. That resolves 4.2 Finding 4.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    18[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m VPC endpoint list is thorough: DynamoDB, S3, Bedrock, Kinesis, KMS, CloudWatch Logs, SageMaker Runtime, Step Functions ([38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mstates[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m), EventBridge ([38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mevents[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m), STS, SES.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    19[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m A dedicated TODO in the Why This Isn't Production-Ready section enumerates DLQ coverage across Step Functions, Kinesis attribution, and Batch Transform job failures. That captures 4.1 Finding 6, 4.2 Finding 6, and 4.3's DLQ pattern as a chapter-wide concern rather than re-litigating it inline.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    20[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m The SDOH-cohort PHI sensitivity paragraph (TODO at the bottom) addresses one of the chapter-wide issues: cohort labels like [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mlow_food_security[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m are derived from screening data and reveal sensitive life circumstances that, in small cohorts within specific geographies, are reidentifying.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    21[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m SES BAA scope, SageMaker Feature Store HIPAA eligibility, and Bedrock per-model eligibility are all flagged with appropriate TODO markers rather than asserted.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    22[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    23[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;192;197;206mThat said, three correctness gaps need attention before publication, and the medium and low items round out the review:[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    24[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    25[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m1[38;2;191;97;106m.[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mThe recipe consistently calls the diabetes prevention program "12-week" and claims it "follows the CDC curriculum."[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m The canonical CDC National DPP is a 12-month program (16 weekly core sessions plus 6 monthly post-core sessions, ~22-26 sessions total over a year). 12-week DPP variants exist in the market, but they are not "the CDC curriculum." This factual mischaracterization runs through The Problem, The Technology, the architecture discussion, and the medium-horizon evaluation discussion, and a healthcare reader will spot it immediately.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    26[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    27[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m2[38;2;191;97;106m.[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mThe pseudocode for [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mscore_eligible_population[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;235;203;139m serializes scoring across programs.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m The outer [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mFOR each program in programs:[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m loop creates three Batch Transform jobs and then calls [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mwait_for_jobs([need_job, engagement_job, uplift_job])[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m before the next program starts. With 6 programs in the recipe's stated scale and ~10-15 minutes per Batch Transform job, this is a 60-90 minute pipeline that should finish in 10-15 minutes if programs are fanned out in parallel. The architecture diagram suggests parallel scoring per program, but the pseudocode reads serial; a reader following the pseudocode will ship a slow pipeline that doesn't match the prerequisites table's "30-90 minutes" claim.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    28[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    29[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m3[38;2;191;97;106m.[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mThe optimistic contact-frequency counter is incremented at outreach send time but the reconciliation path on send failure is named without being specified.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m The [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mtailor_and_dispatch[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m step calls [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mDynamoDB.UpdateItem(... ADD outreach_recent_wellness_count :one ...)[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m and the prose says "Update the contact-frequency counter optimistically. The actual send may fail; reconcile in the engagement-attribution step." Step 7 ([38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mprocess_engagement_event[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m) does not show a decrement on [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mprogram_outreach_failed[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m or on bounce events. Members whose outreach never reached them still consume a slot in their cap, eventually pushing them past [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mMAX_WELLNESS_PER_MONTH[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m and excluding them from future outreach for outreach they never received. Compounded over months, this systematically silences members whose channel preferences are flaky (the same members whose outreach is hardest to deliver, often the same members the equity floors are trying to protect).[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    30[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    31[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;192;197;206mA handful of medium and low findings round out the review: the wellness consent regime doesn't address state-by-state and ADA/GINA-specific requirements, the tracking_id format embeds member_id in plain text, the outreach validator's approved-claims and prohibited-claims lists are mentioned but not specified, the VPC endpoint list misses Athena and Glue, the Step Functions retry semantics on partial Batch Transform completion aren't addressed, the PCP override has no pre-send hold-time semantics for higher-risk recommendations, and the chapter-wide IAM-ARN-scoping and [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140m0.0.0.0/0[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;192;197;206m-egress patterns are repeated.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    32[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    33[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;192;197;206mThe voice is clean throughout: zero em dashes (verified), zero en dashes (verified), 70/30 vendor balance maintained, no marketing-language creep ("robust" appears three times, all technical: "robust, interpretable" describing causal forests, "doubly-robust estimation" as a real causal-inference term, and "robust to alternative matching specifications"). The Honest Take's "the data science is the easiest part" framing and the "wellness-program domain has a long history of vendors with thin evidence" closing are exactly the contrarian-but-correct CC tone the chapter has been collecting.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    34[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    35[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;192;197;206mPriority breakdown: 0 critical, 3 high, 7 medium, 6 low.[K
